answers.answer: Hello,When fasting insulin is over 5 µIU/mL, this indicates a metabolic problem such as pre-diabetes. Excess insulin is defined when levels are equal to or greater than 15 µIU/mL. Your levels of 11 µIU/mL are definitely high and you should consult your physician for the treatment.It is very difficult to precisely confirm a diagnosis without examination and investigations and the answer is based on the medical information provided. For exact diagnosis, you are requested to consult your doctor. I sincerely hope that helps. Take care and please do keep me posted on how you are doing.
